    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "@mikerodent consider testing your code against a 3rd party online service. You would want to monitor possible changes in the service API to be able to respond with deployed fixes ASAP. Isn&#39;t CI tests a good way of doing that? Using a mock will only tell you your own code doesn&#39;t have regressions, but the dependencies still might have changes. using the real service would indicate that your product can actually perform the expected operations in the current environment."
