    "body" : "@mikerodent what a nonsense argument. For exactly the purpose of running tests regularly (every day/hour whatever) or even manually when it is suspected that something has changed in the 3rd party input, it is useful to be able re-run the tests if neither the application code nor the test code have change. Why not use gradle for this purpose? Re-running tests is a perfectly valid scenario, that&#39;s why the option --rerun-tasks exists, as a more helpful user points out in the accepted answer."
