    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Other option would be to add following in your build.gradle:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-none prettyprint-override\"><code>test.outputs.upToDateWhen {false}\n</code></pre>\n<p>To expand on this solution, here is a recipe for kotlin-DSL gradle files (<code>build.gradle.kts</code>) that selects a particular task by name:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-none prettyprint-override\"><code>tasks.named(&quot;your task name&quot;) {\n    outputs.upToDateWhen { false }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
