      "post_id" : 52484259,
      "comment_id" : 138936990,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "In my case, the purpose of re-running tests is to debug the build script. Ostensibly, there are no failed tests, but after some effort I see that the tests were not run after I changed the build script. The source of misbehavior could be: a bug in configuration, a bug in build logic, a bug (or breaking change) in Gradle itself, and, as if these three are not enough, there is that &quot;do not rerun&quot; logic."
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 313216,
      "reputation" : 47819,
      "user_id" : 627727,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 84,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/uOIWL.jpg?s=256",
