  "title" : "How to run Gradle test when all tests are UP-TO-DATE?",
  "body" : "<p>I have my grade script set up.\nWhen I execute the Gradle build, everything is working and it runs the jUnit tests.</p>\n\n<p>After that when I run the Gradle test I get the following:</p>\n\n<pre><code>C:\\Users\\..\\..\\Project&gt;gradle test\n:compileJava UP-TO-DATE\n:processResources UP-TO-DATE\n:classes UP-TO-DATE\n:compileTestJava UP-TO-DATE\n:processTestResources UP-TO-DATE\n:testClasses UP-TO-DATE\n:test UP-TO-DATE\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>When I perform <code>gradle clean</code>, then Gradle build works, of course...\nI want to be able to reset only the tests, not build the whole project: how should I do this?</p>\n"
